Water Stress from High-Volume Hydraulic Fracturing Potentially Threatens
Aquatic Biodiversity and Ecosystem Services in Arkansas, United States

     * Sally Entrekin^*^† Orcid
     * Anne Trainor^‡
     * James Saiers^§
     * Lauren Patterson^∥
     * Kelly Maloney^⊥
     * Joseph Fargione^#
     * Joseph Kiesecker^∇
     * Sharon Baruch-Mordo^∇
     * Katherine Konschnik^○
     * Hannah Wiseman^⧫
     * Jean-Philippe Nicot^^
     * Joseph N. Ryan^¶

   View Author Information
   † Department of Biology, University of Central Arkansas, 201 Donaghey
   Avenue, Conway, Arkansas 72035, United States
   ‡ The Nature Conservancy, African Program, University of Cincinnati,
   820G Rieveschl Hall, Cincinnati, Ohio 45220, United States
   § School of Forestry and Environmental Studies, Yale University, 195
   Prospect St., New Haven, Connecticut 06511, United States
   ∥ Nicholas Institute for Environmental Policy Solutions at Duke
   University, 2111 Campus Drive, Durham North Carolina 27708, United
   States
   ⊥ U.S. Geological Survey, Leetown Science Center, 11649 Leetown Road,
   Kearneysville, West Virginia 25430, United States
   # The Nature Conservancy, 1101 West River Parkway, Suite 200,
   Minneapolis, Minnesota 55415, United States
   ∇ The Nature Conservancy, Global Lands Team, 117 E. Mountain Avenue,
   Suite 201, Fort Collins, Colorado 80524, United States
   ○ Environmental Policy Initiative, Harvard Law School, #4123
   Wasserstein Hall, Cambridge, Massachusetts 02138, United States
   ⧫ Florida State University College of Law, 424 West Jefferson Street,
   Tallahassee, Florida 32306, United States
   ^ Bureau of Economic Geology, Jackson School of Geosciences, The
   University of Texas at Austin, 10100 Burnet Road, Building 130, Austin,
   Texas 78758, United States
   ¶ Department of Civil, Environmental and Architectural Engineering,
   University of Colorado at Boulder, Boulder, Colorado 80309, United
   States
   *Phone/Fax: 501-450-5919; e-mail: [email protected].
   Cite this:Environ. Sci. Technol.20185242349-2358
   Publication Date (Web):January 31, 2018

Publication History

     * Received30 June 2017
     * Accepted3 January 2018
     * Revised29 December 2017
     * Published online31 January 2018
     * Published in issue 20 February 2018

   https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.7b03304
   Copyright © 2018 © 2018 American Chemical Society
   RIGHTS & PERMISSIONS

