            Silver nanoparticles (AgNp) were synthesized using aq. soln.
            of silver nitrate ([110mAg]NO3) with poly(allylamine) as a
            reducing agent and a stabilizer of the AgNp suspension.
            Nanoparticles were characterized by absorption spectroscopy,
            particle size anal., at. force microscopy (AFM), and
            transmission (TEM) electron microscopy. Different size
            nanoparticles (10-30 nm and 70-90 nm) were obtained by varying
            the polymer concn. and reaction time. The application of
            [110mAg]AgNP to environmental studies, using nuclear
            techniques such as in vivo gamma counting and whole-body
            autoradiog., is demonstrated and discussed.
